Analyze Your Data

Address Common Data Issues

Handle common issues that you encounter during data prep for Einstein Discovery.

The following table describes some approaches for handling common data issues when preparing data for analysis.

ISSUE	APPROACH
Extreme Values and Outliers	Einstein Discovery algorithms are sensitive to outliers because those values affect averages (means) and standard deviations in statistical significance calculations. If you find unusual values or outliers, confirm whether these data points are relevant and real.
Missing Values	The most common repair for missing values is imputing a likely or expected value using a mean or computed value from a distribution.
Incorrect Values	Predictive algorithms assume that the input information is correct. If only a few rows have incorrect values, decide what to do. Remove those rows from the analysis, or replace the incorrect values with more correct or average values.
Standardize Categorical Values	For category values, ensure consistent category names.
Apply Fuzzy Matching for Smarter Categorizations
Handle Text Values

Skewed Data	For continuous variables, review the distributions, central tendency, and spread of the variable. If not normally distributed, try to reduce skewness for optimal prediction.
High-Cardinality Fields	High-cardinality fields are categorical attributes that contain many distinct values. Including these attributes vastly increases the dimensionality of the dataset.

Binary Outcomes and Boolean Variables	If a variable has a binary outcome (only two possible values), and those values are represented by numbers, then convert those numeric values to text values.
Ordinal Variables	Ordinal variables are problematic for predictive models. Ordinal data consists of numerical scores on an arbitrary scale that is designed to show ranking in a set of data points.

Duplicate, Redundant, or Highly Correlated Variables	Minimize duplicate, redundant, or other highly correlated variables that carry the same information. Einstein Discovery algorithms perform better without these kinds of collinear variables.

SEE ALSO
Collect, Cleanse, and Optimize Your Data
Handle Quality Alerts
title: Addressing Common Data Issues for Einstein Discovery
